g_sepIdx[g_sepIdx.length] = '3d31a66221616fe28abde730394dc788';
g_searchEnginePlainTextArray['3d31a66221616fe28abde730394dc788'] = 'All important new features of the Data Service are summarized here. For more details on the individual topics, refer to the documentation. Data Service modes As of version 1.4, there are two modes for the Data Service: Stand-alone Data Service All functions including user interface available Integrated Data Service in IIH (Industrial Information Hub) The Data Service no longer has its own user interface. Data retention for assets and variables can now be set directly in the IIH. For additional information on the integration in the IIH, click here:  Integrating Data Service into the IIH Connectivity Suite Connectors The Data Service now supports Connectivity Suite connectors in addition to MQTT connectors. System information dashboard In the System Information dashboard, you can view the information from the System Info connector. You can find additional information here:  Display system information Setting aggregation for variables When creating a variable, you can set an aggregation and significantly improve performance in the Data Service by pre-calculating the data. Pre-calculated aggregations are taken into account when querying the data. This decisively shortens the duration of the query. For example, the aggregations API queries the last month with aggregation \"Sum\".  For this, the aggregation is calculated from the raw data as needed (at 1ms cycle = 2 628 000 000 data points). However, if pre-calculated aggregations have been configured on the variable, the aggregation can be calculated from them (e.g. 1h aggregation configured = 730 data points). For additional information on creating an aggregation, click here:  Creating a variable General Performance improvements Anomaly Detection compatibility The Anomaly Detection app (V1.0, V1.1 and future versions) is only compatible with the standalone Data Service. When the Data Service is integrated into the IIH, it is no longer compatible with Anomaly Detection. Only with Data Service V1.5 will Anomaly Detection be compatible in IIH mode.';
g_sepIdx[g_sepIdx.length] = 'df71ead9c6e698d8e62fa06a7fab8d3f';
g_searchEnginePlainTextArray['df71ead9c6e698d8e62fa06a7fab8d3f'] = 'Description You can install and start the  Data Service app in the catalog of the  Industrial Edge Management (IEM) instance.  Requirement You must be logged into the  Industrial Edge Management (IEM). The  Data Service app was copied to the catalog. You can find more information here:  Copying the Data Service app from the IE Hub to the IEM catalog Procedure To install the  Data Service app, follow these steps: Open the \" Catalog\" tab. Click on the \" Data Service\" tile. The following dialog box opens: Click \" Install\". The \" Install App\" dialog window is displayed. You can see a table with all associated IEDs. Select one or more IEDs on which you want to install the app: You have two options to continue:  Click \" Install Later\" to schedule the date and time of the installation.  Click \" Install Now\" to install the app immediately.  When you click \" Install Now\", you will receive the following message: Click \" Allow\". The installation of the apps is started on the selected IEDs. Result The  Data Service app is listed in the \" My Installed App\" tab.';
g_sepIdx[g_sepIdx.length] = '5f87c115ddfae84a5b516d1030c73942';
g_searchEnginePlainTextArray['5f87c115ddfae84a5b516d1030c73942'] = 'Description In the \" Hierarchy\" tab, you can move assets and their child assets in the hierarchy. Procedure To move an asset, follow these steps: Select the asset you want to move. In the example below, \" Machine_1\". Click on the three dots (ellipsis) in the corresponding row of the selection list. Select \" Move asset\" in the selection window that opens: All assets to which you can move the selected asset are marked with this blue arrow  :  A blue information box appears at the bottom left, indicating that the asset can be moved. Select the target asset and click the blue arrow: Result The moved asset is displayed in the desired position:';
g_sepIdx[g_sepIdx.length] = '2df59a02a5fe196cadd211740ada951d';
g_searchEnginePlainTextArray['2df59a02a5fe196cadd211740ada951d'] = 'After you have installed the  Data Service app on the IED, the app is displayed in the \" Industrial Edge Management\" in the \" My Installed Apps\" view. Requirement The app must be installed on the  Industrial Edge Device (IED). Procedure To start the  Data Service app, follow these steps: Open the start page of the IED by entering the following URL address:  \"https:\\\\[IP address of the IED]\" Log in with \" Username\" and \" Password\": Open the \" Apps\" tab: Click the  Data Service tile to open the app in the browser. Result The  Data Service app opens in the browser:';
